  quests: [
    {
      id: "02000000007B0000",
      title: "Water Processing",
      x: 4,
      y: 4,
      tasks: [
        {
          id: "03000000007B0000",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:thermal_evaporation_controller"
        },
        {
          id: "03000000007B0001",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:thermal_evaporation_valve",
          count: 2
        },
        {
          id: "03000000007B0002",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:thermal_evaporation_block",
          count: 64
        }
      ],
      description: ["Thermal Evaporation Plants (TEP) uses heat, either generated from machines, or from the sun. It can turn Water into Brine, or Brine into Lithium.", "To build the TEP, you need to make a 4x4 solid base out of Thermal Evaporation Blocks, then make walls (with corners) on top of that base with Thermal Evaporation Blocks.", "On the structure, you will need 1 Controller and at least 2 Valves. The corner blocks MUST be Thermal Evaporation Blocks. It has a minimum height of 3 blocks (incl the base) and a max height of 17 (incl the solar panels).", "There's 2 ways for the TEP to generate heat. It can either collect heat by itself, which depends on biome (Desert is best). You can speed up heat collection by putting Advanced Solar Panels on top, on the corners, with Thermal Evaporation Blocks in between. It must be daytime for it to collect Heat.", "Alternatively you can pump in Heat with Fuelwood or Resistive Heaters. This does require an additional Valve to be attatched to the TEP, but eliminates the night cycle and biome problems.", "The height of the TEP increases its in and output buffer, but also increases the amount of heat it can hold, and thus increasing the production rate.", "", "TEP does, unlike every other multiblock structure, not accept Structural Glass"],
      icon: "mekanism:thermal_evaporation_controller",
      dependencies: ["02000000007C0000"],
      rewards: [
        {
          id: "04000000007B0000",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanismgenerators:advanced_solar_generator",
          count: 4
        },
        {
          id: "04000000007B0064",
