    {
      id: "0200000000990000",
      title: "Pew pew pew! / Heating up",
      x: 11,
      y: 8,
      tasks: [
        {
          id: "0300000000990000",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:laser",
          count: 5
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000990001",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:laser_amplifier"
        }
      ],
      description: ["The laser is both your first and last step towards the Fusion Reactor.", "The Reactor needs a burst of heat, before it can kickstart, and the lasers allows that by firing RF into it.", "There's 2 blocks, the Laser and the Laser Amplifier.", "The Lasers shoots a laser, and the Laser Amplifiers combines these lasers into one big beam.", "You can focus Amplifiers into more Amplifiers.", "You want your final Amplifier to line up with the Laser Focus Matrix of the Fusion Reactor.", "You want at least 800mil RF in the final Amplifier to do the kickstart in one big burst (set the Amplifiers redstone mode to \"High\"), and each Laser only transfers 2000 RF/t, so it can be quite a slow process if you don't have a lot of Lasers.", "", "WARNING: The Lasers will break blocks and damage mobs/players, and the stronger the laser is, the faster it breaks/more damage it deals. They will not break any Laser Focus Matrixes. The Laser reaches for 64 blocks, and can extended with Amplifiers."],
      icon: "mekanism:laser",
      dependencies: ["02000000007F0000"],
      rewards: [
        {
          id: "0400000000990000",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:laser",
          count: 5
        },
        {
          id: "0400000000990001",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:laser_amplifier"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      id: "02000000009A0000",
      title: "Fueling up",
      x: 13,
      y: 8,
      tasks: [
        {
          id: "03000000009A0000",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:chemical_infuser"
        }
      ],
      description: ["D-T Fuel is what is needed to do the Kickstart in the Reactor.", "&cNow, DO NOT PUMP D-T FUEL DIRECTLY INTO THE REACTOR, &runless you can keep up with its demand (1000mb/t), which does result in 100mil rf/t generated.", "The Fusion Reactor will make its own D-T Fuel, and take depending on your Injection Rate (minimum 2).", "To make the D-T Fuel, you have to put Deterium and Tritium into a Chemical Infuser. The only use for the D-T Fuel is to fill up the Hohlraums (unless you pump directly into the Reactor)."],
