          count: 9
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000A10003",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanismgenerators:electromagnetic_coil",
          count: 9
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000A10004",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:pressure_disperser",
          count: 8
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000A10005",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanismgenerators:rotational_complex"
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000A10006",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanismgenerators:turbine_rotor",
          count: 2
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000A10007",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanismgenerators:turbine_blade",
          count: 4
        }
      ],
      description: ["The Turbine is one of Mekanisms bigger power generators. It is a Multiblock, that runs on Steam.", "It is a multistructure that can be turned and flipped in any direction, but in the explanation we're going to have it standing, with the Steam at the top, and the blades going down.", "The materials from the Crafting Task is enough for a 5x5x6. Like the other Mekanism multistructures, the edges must be the base block (Turbine Casing in this case).", "On the top part, you want Turbine Vents. These can be on level or above the Rotational Complex.", "On the top level inside the Turbine, you have to place your Electromagnetic Coils. These just have to connect to each other and the Rotational Complex.", "Below those you need your Pressure Dispersers. Like the Boiler, these must cover the entire layer out to the walls.", "In the middle of the Pressure Dispersers, you want to place your Rotational Complex.", "From the Rotational Complex to the bottom, you place the Turbine Rotors, and the put your Turbine Blades on the Rotors.", "The Valves can go anywhere on the walls (except the corners). The Valves is both Steam input and Power Output.", "The power output from the turbine, depends on the amount of Steam coming in to the turbine. More steam = more power.", " In the Statistics window you can see what is currently limiting your power generation (in the case of the 5x5x6, it's the amount of blades). The fix to this is to build it taller."],
      icon: "mekanismgenerators:turbine_blade",
      dependencies: ["02000000009D0000"],
      rewards: [
        {
          id: "0400000000A10000",
          type: "item",
          item: "mekanism:structural_glass",
          count: 46
        }
      ]
